entry.content: Russia Rejects Peace, Wants To Settle It On Battlefield #ukraine #russia Russia has rejected Ukraine’s peace plan because they want to “settle it on the Battlefield” instead. Just this past week, Ukraine struck the Black Sea Headquarters in Crimea - killing the commander of the Black Sea Fleet. Meanwhile American tanks have finally arrived in Ukraine with Depleted uranium rounds. And while Ukraine’s counteroffensive has been moving slower than expected, their shaping operation in Crimea has seen great success.

entry.content: US Deploys F-16s To Enforce No-Fly Zone #usa #ukraine The US has deployed F-16s to Romania to enforce the new no fly zone. The No-Fly Zone extends 30 kilometers from Romania’s eastern border and will allow them to shoot down any missiles or drones approaching their borders. This comes after Russia kept hitting Romania when they were attacking Ukraine.

entry.content: Canadian Pilot Changes Call Sign To What?! #canada #uk Yesterday a Canadian fighter jet changed its call sign to “D**K69” while it was flying over the UK. Canada says it’s investigating the name change, adding that it was inappropriate and unapproved. Call signs contain four letters and two numbers. They are assigned to pilots and usually remain unchanged. And this Canadian pilot changed their call sign from BLDE11 to D**K69. They could be facing a stiff punishment.

entry.content: Gamer Leaks Classified Document To Win War Thunder Argument #usa #warthunder For the third time this month, gamers have leaked restricted military documents on the war thunder forums. This time it’s the manual to the Apache helicopter which was supposed to be for the DoD only. Earlier this month, a user leaked part of the manual to the F-117 Nighthawk’s flight manual. War Thunder’s dedication to realism is its Achilles heal as players often resort to leaking classified documents in order to settle online arguments… which has happened at least 13 times.
